{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Reference [46] proposed an effective data augmentation method based on traffic sign recognition to tackle the problem of insufficient samples.",
    "Building upon the YOLOv3 algorithm, they obtained mutual recognition of traffic signs and used the Canny operator to automatically generate masks for these signs.",
    "To simulate variations in viewpoints as seen in real scenarios, perspective transformation was applied to the traffic sign recognition.",
    "This perspective transformation projected two-dimensional images onto another plane, thus generating a sufficient amount of training data.In addition, certain small targets, such as traffic signs or traffic lights, might not be very prominent.",
    "Data augmentation can enhance the model's ability to detect them by adjusting their size, position, and rotation to simulate different perspectives and distances."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Reference [46] proposed an effective data augmentation method based on traffic sign recognition to tackle the problem of insufficient samples."
  ]
}